The paper focuses on the application of convolutional neural networks (CNN) for automated detection and localisation of building defects from images, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The use of pre-trained CNN classifiers and class activation mapping (CAM) also suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and robotics (cs.RO) sub-categories. Additionally, the potential for scaling up and using mobile devices and drones for real-time detection of defects indicates a possible connection to multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
